      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "VERY TEMPTING (8) went back last start then worked home well from a long way out to finish just a nose from the winner in second at Bendigo over 1650m, that run following his ninth there two runs back. Shouldn't spend a penny from this draw and the sprint lane may come in handy. Won't find this any harder and he can take this out. STANDANDELIVER (2) was out of the money two runs ago then broke after suffering interference and finished eighth last start over 1650m at Bendigo, arriving 40 metres behind the winner. A nice draw on the front line this time should ensure a cosy run. Big chance with any luck in this similar assignment. MIKI MARK (6) is looming as a real threat after a better effort last start, finishing third at Kilmore over 2180m. FAKE CULLECTION (5) showed pleasing improvement last time out when third over 1650m at Bendigo. In the mix.",
